## Failure modes

| What can go wrong | How mtix behaves | What you do |
|---|---|---|
| **PG unreachable** during snapshot | Client hook warns and exits 0; server-side check fails the push. | Restore PG connectivity. The push retries cleanly once PG is back. |
| **PG unreachable** during a mutation | Mutation aborts with a clear error. No silent retry. | Wait for PG; rerun the command. Investigate the outage. |
| **Hook bypassed client-side** (`git push --no-verify`) | Server-side enforcement (pre-receive or GitHub Action) rejects the push. tasks.json freshness is guaranteed at the server boundary. | No remediation needed; the server-side check is the gate. |
| **Schema mismatch** (developer running an older binary) | Store init refuses with `audit_log table not found` or unknown future-version error. | Pin the team's mtix binary version in your dev env documentation; gate upgrades through the same change-management you use for code. |
| **`audit_log` full** (storage exhausted) | Mutation transactions abort. No data is written without an audit row. | Run `mtix audit prune` to archive old rows immediately; provision more PG storage. The append-only invariant is preserved across the prune (archive files are restorable). |
| **Two devs push simultaneously** | Both PG mutations commit (independent rows). Git rejects the slower push as non-fast-forward. | Pull, re-run `mtix snapshot`, push. Server-side check verifies the merged snapshot still matches PG. |
| **Network partition** between CLI and PG | Mutation aborts; no half-committed state due to PG MVCC. | Retry once connectivity is restored. |
| **PG superuser disables triggers** | Audit log is now mutable. mtix has no in-process detection. | Mitigated by archive-to-immutable-storage: even if PG-side audit is tampered, the cold-storage archive provides the canonical history. Detect via routine archive-vs-PG audit comparison. |
| **Audit archive upload fails** | mtix `audit prune --archive-dir` writes the local archive but does not upload. The local file is the source of truth until uploaded. | Monitor your upload job; alert on failure. Do not delete the local archive until upload is confirmed. |
| **DSN leaked** | mtix has no in-process detection of credential exfiltration. | Rotate the PG password immediately; revoke the leaked role; review `pg_stat_activity` for unfamiliar sessions. |
| **PG provider compromise** | Out of mtix scope. | Use a provider with documented security posture; encrypt sensitive task content client-side if needed. |

